<script>

    
    (function($scope) {
    
 
    console.log('Hello');

    let keys = {};

    document.addEventListener('keydown', (event) => {
    if (event.repeat) return;
    
    if (event.key != "CapsLock") {
        keys[event.key] = true;
        let msg = {"payload": keys, "topic": "keydown"};
        $scope.send(msg);
    }
    });

    document.addEventListener('keyup', (event) => {
    var keyName = event.key;
    var keyCode = event.code;
    delete keys[event.key];
    let msg = {"payload": keys, "topic": "keyup"};
    $scope.send(msg);

    },{capture: true});
    })(scope);
</script>

format:
<template>
    <!-- Any HTML can go here -->
    <button class="my-class2" onclick="onClick()">My Button</button>
</template>

<script>
    /* Write any JavaScript here */
    // add our onClick function to the window object to make it accessible by the HTML <button>
    window.onClick = function () {
        alert('Button has been clicked')
    }

    // Use send() function to pass on data back into Node-RED:
    this.send('Component has loaded')

    // Subscribe to the incoming msg's
    this.$socket.on('msg-input:' + this.id, function(msg) {
        // do stuff with the message
        alert('message received: ' + msg.payload + 'from' + this.id)
    })
</script>

<style>
    /* define any styles here - supports raw CSS */
    .my-class2 {
        color: green;
    }
</style>
